"{\"uid\": \"rollingstone.com-culture-culture-features-olympians-main-character-1235071606\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"ByCT Jones  What's better than cheering on overtwo hundred countriescompeting in increasingly obscure sports on a world stage?\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 126, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Making these specific and increasinglyunique athletesstars in their own right, of course.\", \"from\": 127, \"to\": 216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition to competing on the field (mat, pitch, range, whatever) some athletes participating in the2024 Paris Olympicshave become internet main characters of the day for their stellar performances.\", \"from\": 217, \"to\": 417, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's an introduction to some athletes who will probably be dominating your thoughts - and timelines - for the foreseeable future.\", \"from\": 419, \"to\": 550, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Ilona Maherfirst became an online sensation during her Olympic debut at the 2020 Tokyo Games, which she spent sharing behind-the-scenes looks at the Olympic Village to her skyrocketing follower count onTikTok.\", \"from\": 552, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 552, \"end\": 557, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"score\": 0.9999999998472049, \"rank\": 1.524950781024527e-10, \"text\": \"Ilona\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ilona_Mitrecey\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She entered the 2024 Paris Games as an established influencer online with 2 million followers but quickly re-cemented her status as an internet queen with humorous videos - like meeting CoCo Gauff, Simone Biles, and Snoop Dogg, modeling the divisive Team USA uniforms, and strongly shutting down haters who comment on her body and size.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 1098, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 948, \"end\": 958, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"CoCo Gauff\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Coco_Gauff\"}, {\"begin\": 960, \"end\": 972, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Simone Biles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Simone_Biles\"}, {\"begin\": 978, \"end\": 988, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}, {\"begin\": 1012, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9798776230990277, \"rank\": 0.01801343131915809, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Underneath Maher's humor is a platform that highlights pride and acceptance in oneself -\\u00a0beliefs that she's continued to promote to her viewers.\", \"from\": 1099, \"to\": 1243, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And nothing says I am not afraid to be strong and tough like stiff-arming your way to a bronze medal.\", \"from\": 1244, \"to\": 1345, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Which one @paris2024 @Team USA @Olympics  Delicious.pic.twitter.com/flpxWfrr1M  Congratulations to the USA Women's Rugby team!\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1473, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1450, \"end\": 1453, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999981626122971, \"rank\": 1.8371190291301808e-06, \"text\": \"USA\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\ud83d\\udcf8:@ilona_maherpic.twitter.com/REG5PjTCKZ  While in Paris, Maher even convinced former Philadelphia Eagles starJason Kelceto become the celeb sponsor of the U.S Rugby team, taking after rapperFlavor Flav's sponsorship of the U.S. women's Water Polo team.\", \"from\": 1474, \"to\": 1727, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1526, \"end\": 1531, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.214723113852694e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1561, \"end\": 1580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia_Eagles\", \"score\": 0.999999998893145, \"rank\": 1.0725816975534574e-09, \"text\": \"Philadelphia Eagles\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q12973014\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia_Eagles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philadelphia_Eagles\"}, {\"begin\": 1712, \"end\": 1722, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.7754260653644344e-19, \"text\": \"Water Polo\", \"types\": [\"Q349\", \"Q1914636\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Water_polo\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelce even got to wear with his very own personalized Maher button-up.\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1798, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Long live Maher, an American treasure.Editor's picksThe 250 Greatest Albums of the 21st Century So FarThe 100 Best TV Episodes of All TimeThe 500 Greatest Albums of All Time100 Best Movies of the 21st Century  Beyond the Clark Kent-esque aesthetics ofStephen Nedoroscikis a pommel horse expert, one whose showing at the Men's Gymnastics final clinched the United States men'sartistic gymnasticsteam bronze - their first medal in almost 16 years.\", \"from\": 1799, \"to\": 2244, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1820, \"end\": 1828, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.999999999395186, \"rank\": 5.422555301472712e-10, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2126, \"end\": 2136, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.999999987665433, \"rank\": 1.2334681930804953e-08, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}, {\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2169, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999930145657583, \"rank\": 6.985323369443035e-06, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nedoroscik first captured eyes and hearts during the final when cameras caught him preparing for his event by leaning back and closing his eyes.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2389, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Was he sleeping?\", \"from\": 2390, \"to\": 2406, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Nope, he later toldTodayhe was doing \\\"breathing exercises\\\" and visualizing his routine in his head.\", \"from\": 2407, \"to\": 2506, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But the look, and Nedoroscik's perfect ending performance, turned the gymnast into a meme at record speed.\", \"from\": 2507, \"to\": 2613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Obsessed with this guy on the US men's gymnastics team who's only job is pommel horse, so he just sits there until he's activated like a sleeper agent, whips off his glasses like Clark Kent and does a pommel horse routine that helps deliver the team its first medal in 16 years.pic.twitter.com/0D1ZqJjFa1  me liking every tweet about Steve the pommel horse hero and his glassespic.twitter.com/kQhyRDMVKV  MY HEARTpic.twitter.com/zh6KCTpwtk  If dominating on the pommel horse wasn't enough, Nedoroscik can also solve a Rubik's Cube incredibly fast - under 30 seconds\\u00a0- a skill he's more than happy to share with anyone who asks.\", \"from\": 2615, \"to\": 3242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2646, \"end\": 2648, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.6045453103557935, \"rank\": 0.5708055762862548, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2795, \"end\": 2805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9917326964346783e-54, \"text\": \"Clark Kent\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Superman\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He does have a girlfriend though, former Penn State gymnast Tess McCracken (or Mrs. Pommel Horse, as she refers to herself on X), so do not go too crazy.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3285, \"end\": 3295, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"score\": 0.9525139584987897, \"rank\": 0.025080192368052895, \"text\": \"Penn State\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Penn_State_Nittany_Lions_football\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The only word I can think of to describe South Korean sharpshooter Kim Yeji is sickening.\", \"from\": 3398, \"to\": 3487, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3446, \"end\": 3452, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"score\": 0.9991250413428829, \"rank\": 0.0008757245615133317, \"text\": \"Korean\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Korean_language\"}, {\"begin\": 3466, \"end\": 3469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2807620736480353e-21, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}, {\"begin\": 3470, \"end\": 3474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.291418027078325e-34, \"text\": \"Yeji\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Itzy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And I am not the only one who thinks so.\", \"from\": 3488, \"to\": 3528, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It took less than 40 seconds for Kim to make the shot that got her silver at the 2024 ParisOlympics.\", \"from\": 3529, \"to\": 3629, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2807620736480353e-21, \"text\": \"Kim\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kim_Kardashian\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But her shooting pose, complete with special sharpshooter spectacles, a cocked hip, and her daughter's toy elephant quickly cemented her status as a legendary performer.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3799, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There have been thirst tweets, lesbian adoration, fan edits, and drawings comparing Kim to some of the strongest anime characters of all time.Related ContentPeople Use AI to Justify Bad Behavior.\", \"from\": 3800, \"to\": 3995, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3832, \"end\": 3839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lesbian\", \"score\": 0.9994846143632701, \"r